31/05/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Prime Minister-designate Hari Kostov presents his cabinet to parliament Monday (31 May), with a vote planned afterwards. 
Kostov is expected to retain all the incumbent ministers and to nominate Siljan Avramovski, the current head of the security and counterintelligence agency, to succeed him as interior minister.
In other news, Croatian Army Chief of Staff General Josip Lucic is wrapping up a two-day visit to Skopje. 
He and Macedonian counterpart Major General Gjorgji Bojadjiev have been exchanging experiences on preparations and reforms related to NATO membership. 
(Utrinski Vesnik, Makfax - 31/05/04; A1 TV - 30/05/04)
